Description:
The versatile entertainer
This two bedroom cream clinker, spacious with Art Deco detail proves the most versatile of homes with its studios offering an additional two bedrooms. But more than that, this home's main drawcard is its effortless entertaining. A gourmet CaesarStone kitchen with 900mm Falcon range is flanked by L-shaped lounge and dining, and lavish covered alfresco complete with cafe curtains, spa, heating and fans offering all-weather entertaining. North facing rear gardens extend outdoor entertaining, while stacker doors between lounge and dining means the home is as open or private as you want. Add to this a bright bathroom, hardwood floors, OFP, heating/cooling, solar panels, water tank, ample storage plus OSP in a serene cul-de-sac near Moreland Station, Sydney Road, parks and schools.
Insights: 28 Hall Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2020 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Main Attraction
Expressions of Interest closes 3/3/2020 at 5:00pm
In true Coburg heartland this two bedroom Victorian opens the door to an exciting future. A stroll to trains, trams, buses, cafes, restaurants, Sydney Road and Coburg Market, the semi-detached home retains elegant period details. A long hallway leads past the front living room and bedrooms to a dining room, beyond which is a kitchen hosting a gas stove. Featuring a relaxing shaded area, the rear garden has great possibilities for entertaining. A wide electric roller door accesses a right of way, enabling secure off street parking whilst high ceilings, rosettes, deep cornices, a grand archway and polished floorboards exude character inside. Opportunities to easily add enhancements are plentiful so get creative: seize the potential and shape a fantastic lifestyle!

Description:
Art Deco Allure with Modern Family Credentials
Surrounded by established gardens on a substantial corner allotment, this gorgeous period home provides an idyllic environment of quality and versatility - all in a blissfully quiet yet enviably convenient Coburg neighbourhood. Retaining its authentic elegance, the home's refined interior showcases three spacious bedrooms (all with built-in robes) and two contemporary-style bathrooms - both with stone-top vanities. The warm and inviting lounge is adjoined by an equally graceful dining room, plus the added appeal of an open-plan living/meals area and superb stone-bench kitchen complete with breakfast bar, Blanco cooking appliances and Asko dishwasher. High ceilings throughout, the home also boasts multi-zone ducted heating/refrigerated cooling, alarm system, original lead-light windows, stained timberwork and solid hardwood floors. Bi-folds from the living area reveal an al-fresco entertaining deck and delightful backyard garden, along with a versatile studio/workshop and secure carport (r/c rollerdoor to Ewen Street). Moments from the open spaces of Robinson Reserve, it's also walking distance to Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and city-bound trams, it's also close to local parks and popular primary schools as well as easy access to Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct.

Description:
When Convenience Is Key
When location and convenience are key this spacious two bedroom townhouse perfectly fits the bill. Sophisticated minimal maintenance design is matched by a lifestyle location that boasts easy access to bustling Sydney Road trams, shopping and restaurants, Moreland Station, parks and bike paths. Spotlessly presented with a reverse floorplan designed to maximise light and space, this property features gleaming hardwood floors though expansive living and dining. The living room opening to a breezy balcony and dining showcasing a sleek CaesarStone kitchen featuring Bosch/Omega appliances. Privately zoned bedrooms, one with access to a quaint garden courtyard, share a gleaming modern bathroom with stone topped vanity. A Euro laundry, heating/cooling and garage with remote and internal access only add to its appeal.

Description:
Eternal Elegance with Instant Appeal
In a leafy streetscape well south of Bell Street, this gorgeous Californian Bungalow delivers an environment of immediate enjoyment and inner-urban convenience along with plenty of room to further enhance and expand in the future (STCA). Beyond the landscaped front garden and captivating facade, discover an immaculate interior comprising three generous bedrooms (large master with built-in robes) and updated central bathroom. Add to this a wonderfully elegant formal lounge and adjoining dining room leading through to the timber-top kitchen with dishwasher and adjoining meals area. Along with ducted heating and refrigerated cooling for year-round comfort, the home also includes a modern laundry with ample storage cupboards, high ornate ceilings, original lead-light windows, stained timberwork and solid timber floors. French doors reveal a substantial backyard with decking, cool cubby house and high hedges for added privacy, plus an exposed aggregate driveway for multiple off-street parking. Walking distance to local primary schools (Coburg West and St Fidelis) and all public transport options, it's also close to popular parks, cafes and shopping precincts, as well as easy access to Citylink/Tullamarine Freeway. Land Size: 13.8 x 33.3 = 459sqm Approximately

Description:
Parkland Views, Urban Lifestyle
Resort style living is only one of the lifestyle benefits presented by this spacious single bedroom apartment, part of the coveted Merriview Place complex. Opposite Merri Creek parklands, near the bustle of Sydney Road, transport including Coburg Station, local Farmers Markets and parks, its tranquil setting belies the vibrant lifestyle on offer. Neatly presented and big on space with 68m2 (approx.) internally, this sundrenched apartment with Merri Creek views as a backdrop, features Oak flooring in an open plan living domain, stylish well-ordered kitchen with Miele dishwasher and bright balcony. Add to this a communal pool and BBQ facilities making options for entertaining both inside and out easy, while a spacious bedroom with ensuite and walk-in robe, separate laundry, powder room, split system heating/cooling, secure entry, lift access and car space, make this one not to miss.

Description:
Key To Dynamic Living
High end appointments fill this bright and brand new two bedroom townhouse, situated moments to tempting cafes, popular Coburg Market, lively Sydney Road and a range of transport options. From lustrous polished floorboards to sweeping stone surfaces, the ground level is a stylish vision of open plan relaxation. A range of Bosch appliances and great storage further distinguish the kitchen, there's plentiful living and dining space and a sliding glass door leads to a private northerly courtyard with both covered and open space. Sun-filled double bedrooms above host mirrored built-in robes and share a luxe fully tiled bathroom with rainfall shower and deep freestanding bath. A laundry/second toilet, heating/cooling and automatic garage add even more appeal to this glamorous home.

Description:
An exquisite 1930s gem: polished to perfection
In an enclave of quality homes, this picturesque California Bungalow has been meticulously renovated for family living. With the special appeal of a cleverly designed upper-level fourth bedroom/second living area, this light-filled residence offers three double bedrooms opening from a central hall; an expansive living and dining room open to a well-equipped kitchen (premium fittings), covered entertaining deck and tranquil garden; plus a stunning refitted bathroom (bath and shower) and adjoining powder room. Close to schools, tram routes and shopping centres, this delightful home includes off-street parking and features polished timber floors, split-system air conditioning and ducted heating.

Description:
Light and Space with Every Coburg Advantage
An exceptional low-maintenance lifestyle/investment opportunity, this single-level home is sure to make a lasting impression with its versatile floorplan, value-adding potential and enviable inner-urban convenience. Every room filled with natural light, the home's well-presented interior comprises three double bedrooms (two with built-in robes), neat bathroom and separate WC. Adding to its appeal is a separate lounge at the front and spacious open living/meals/kitchen area to the rear. Features include ducted heating, alarm system and NBN connection, north-facing courtyard with large undercover patio and high fences for privacy, plus a single lock-up garage and additional driveway parking space. A short stroll to the open spaces of Robinson Reserve, it's also close to Sydney Road cafes, restaurants and city-bound trams, local parks and popular primary schools as well as easy access to Coburg Station and renowned shopping precinct.

Description:
Federation flavour, timeless appeal
From lofty ceilings to delicate details blended with a modern kitchen and relaxing outdoor spaces, this three bedroom period home exudes appeal in a corner position near Coburg Market. Complementing a central living room is a kitchen/meals filled with quality appliances, from names including Bosch and Electrolux, matched with dark stone countertops. A covered entertaining area awaits outside along with handy places to grow delicious fresh produce. Well proportioned bedrooms offer robes and the neat bathroom teams with a full laundry. Additional features include polished floorboards, high ceilings with rosettes, coloured glass, ducted heating and a reverse cycle air conditioner, plus there's OSP for two. Stroll to transport, playgrounds, True North cafe and buzzing Sydney Road.
